      • getMatching

        default DataSet getMatching(Map<DataStructureComponent<Component.Identifier,?,?>,ScalarValue<?,?,?>> keyValues)
        Create a new DataSet by filtering this DataSet's DataPoints matching the specified values for some identifiers.
        Parameters:
        keyValues - A Map containing values for some of this DataSet Component.Identifiers. If the map is empty, the result is this DataSet.
        Returns:
        A new DataSet of matching DataPoints, eventually empty.

      • filteredMappedJoin

        DataSet filteredMappedJoin(DataSetMetadata metadata,
                           DataSet other,
                           BiPredicate<DataPoint,DataPoint> filter,
                           BinaryOperator<DataPoint> merge)
        Creates a new DataSet by joining DataPoints of this and another DataSet by the common identifiers.
        Parameters:
        metadata - The structure the new DataSet must conform to.
        other - another DataSet that will be joined to this DataSet.
        filter - a BiPredicate used to select only a subset of the joined DataPoints.
        merge - a BinaryOperator that merges two selected joined DataPoints together into one.
        Returns:
        The new DataSet.

      • filteredMappedJoin

        default DataSet filteredMappedJoin(DataSetMetadata metadata,
                                   DataSet other,
                                   BinaryOperator<DataPoint> merge)
        Creates a new DataSet by joining DataPoints of this and another DataSet by the common identifiers. The same as filteredMappedJoin(metadata, other, (a, b) -> true, merge).
        Parameters:
        metadata - The structure the new DataSet must conform to.
        other - another DataSet that will be joined to this DataSet.
        merge - a BinaryOperator that merges two selected joined DataPoints together into one.
        Returns:
        The new DataSet.

      • streamByKeys

        <A,T,TT> Stream<T> streamByKeys(Set<DataStructureComponent<Component.Identifier,?,?>> keys,
                                Map<DataStructureComponent<Component.Identifier,?,?>,ScalarValue<?,?,?>> filter,
                                Collector<DataPoint,A,TT> groupCollector,
                                BiFunction<TT,Map<DataStructureComponent<Component.Identifier,?,?>,ScalarValue<?,?,?>>,T> finisher)
        Perform a computation on each of the groups of the DataPoints of this DataSet which have the same value for each of (a subset of) its Component.Identifiers. The same as streamByKeys(keys, Collections.emptyMap(), groupMapper).
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the result of the computation.
        Parameters:
        keys - the Component.Identifiers used to group the keys.
        filter - a Map of Component.Identifier's values used to exclude matching groups from the computation.
        groupCollector - a Collector applied to each group to produce the final result
        Returns:
        a Stream of <T> objects containing the result of the computation for each group.
